geneVariantDescriptions.description: RAD51C M1? indicates a disruption of the methionine (M) start codon with an unknown translational effect on the Rad51c protein. M1? has not been characterized, however, a version of Rad51c utilizing an alternate methionine at codon 10 decreases mitomycin C sensitivity similar to full-length Rad51c (PMID: 12966089), and therefore, its effect on Rad51c function is unknown (PubMed, Jan 2020).

references.title: Identification of functional domains in the RAD51L2 (RAD51C) protein and its requirement for gene conversion.
